Why: (1) upstream's finish_encode error path returns without
v4l2_m2m_job_finish, leaking the m2m job; the next STREAMOFF then deadlocks in
v4l2_m2m_cancel_job (D-state with the device mutex held, VPU unusable until
power cycle). Log the firmware error and error the buffers instead. (2) The
coded (bitstream) sizeimage is clamped in try_fmt/s_fmt, mirroring the decoder
clamp (patch 0009), bounding the coded-buffer allocations from the fixed pool.

